          <td style="background-color:#F0F4F8;padding:32px 36px 28px 36px;">

            <div style="font-family:'GT Flexa Extended','GT Flexa','Barlow Condensed','Oswald',sans-serif;font-size:11px;font-weight:700;color:#00A1C4;letter-spacing:0.18em;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:22px;;line-height:1.6"></div>

            <div style="font-family:'Aktiv Grotesk','aktiv-grotesk','Helvetica Neue','Arial',sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-weight:400;color:#1E293B;margin-bottom:22px;line-height:1.6;text-align:justify;; font-weight: normal;; font-weight: normal;; font-weight: normal;; font-weight: normal;; font-weight: normal;">Dear Investor,</div>

            <div style="font-family:'Aktiv Grotesk','aktiv-grotesk','Helvetica Neue','Arial',sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-weight:700;color:#1E293B;line-height:1.6;text-align:justify;margin-bottom:22px;; font-weight: normal;; font-weight: normal;; font-weight: normal;; font-weight: normal;; font-weight: normal;">The market rose 5.4% and finished at an <span style="font-weight:700;color:#1E293B;">all-time high</span>, thanks to <span style="font-weight:700;color:#1E293B;">reduced geopolitical tensions and strength in the innovation sectors</span>.</div>

            <div style="font-family:'Aktiv Grotesk','aktiv-grotesk','Helvetica Neue','Arial',sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-weight:300;color:#334155;line-height:1.6;text-align:justify;margin-bottom:22px;; font-weight: normal;; font-weight: normal;; font-weight: normal;; font-weight: normal;; font-weight: normal;">Our market view continued to be <span style="font-weight:700;color:#1E293B;">very positive</span>. Our sectoral equity allocation also remained <span style="font-weight:700;color:#1E293B;">tilted toward high-growth and innovative companies</span> to a significant extent.</div>

            <div style="font-family:'Aktiv Grotesk','aktiv-grotesk','Helvetica Neue','Arial',sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-weight:700;color:#1E293B;line-height:1.6;text-align:justify;margin-bottom:22px;; font-weight: normal;; font-weight: normal;; font-weight: normal;; font-weight: normal;; font-weight: normal;">In a <span style="font-weight:700;color:#1E293B;">very volatile market, our systematic allocation delivered double-digit gains (+13.2%)</span>. We maintained our bullish stance during this month of <span style="font-weight:700;color:#1E293B;">quarterly earnings and with Fed Chairman Jerome Powell in focus</span>. <span style="font-weight:700;color:#1E293B;">Headlines were difficult to navigate, notably because of the Iran conflict</span>.</div>

            <div style="font-family:'Aktiv Grotesk','aktiv-grotesk','Helvetica Neue','Arial',sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-weight:300;color:#334155;line-height:1.6;text-align:justify;margin-bottom:22px;; font-weight: normal;; font-weight: normal;; font-weight: normal;; font-weight: normal;; font-weight: normal;">Our long/short equity portfolio contributed positively to the fund with a <span style="font-weight:700;color:#1E293B;">20.1% performance</span>. We were <span style="font-weight:700;color:#1E293B;">heavily invested in the space sector</span>, notably outside the US. Names like <span style="font-weight:700;color:#1E293B;">Astroscale and the two Creotech companies</span> rose notably in relation to the <span style="font-weight:700;color:#1E293B;">SpaceX IPO</span>. As our market view became less bullish by the end of the month, we <span style="font-weight:700;color:#1E293B;">considerably reduced our exposure</span> to the sector, as we are starting June.</div>

            <div style="font-family:'Aktiv Grotesk','aktiv-grotesk','Helvetica Neue','Arial',sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-weight:300;color:#334155;line-height:1.75;text-align:justify;; font-weight: normal;; font-weight: normal;; font-weight: normal;; font-weight: normal;; font-weight: normal;">Please, find our Taranis Market Sentiment monthly report for May 2026 by <a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1wxrZ7l2foGgCnc4TGPRBLXxN0VSLRRqx/view?usp=sharing" style="color: #0066cc; text-decoration: underline;">clicking here</a>.</div>

